  <row>
    <panel>
      <html>
        <b>Mpool Fill</b>
      <hr/>
      <p>How much data is being held in mpool on each indexer.</p>
      <p>Should be between 0 and 2GB in size, lower values are better. Horizontal lines are 512MB (original setting) and 2GB (updated) for reference.</p>
      <p>Ideal state is all lines are grouped together and no big spikes in usage that don't recover quickly. A plateau at 2GB indicates that the search peer can not reclaim memory fast enough and will block replication and ingestion queues.</p>
    </html>
